   <body>
      <p>A Program Manager or a Program Analyst or any user who has permission to create a program can create or manage the program from the contract or from a stand-alone program. Billing Programs are associated with agreements and managed as part of the agreement life cycle. Programs are associated with an agreement. When agreements are activated, programs are activated.</p>
      <p>Agreement life cycle statuses supported in conjunction with the program are as follows:</p>
      <p>Agreement Status</p>
      <p>
         <table>
            <tgroup cols="3">
               <colspec colname="col1"/>
               <colspec colname="col2"/>
               <colspec colname="col3"/>
               <thead>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Status</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Transition</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Description</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </thead>
               <tbody>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Request</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry/>
                     <entry>
                        <p>New Agreement.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>In Amendment</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>From Activated</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Programs are amended independently from Agreements.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Activated</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>From Request or after Amendment</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>When the Agreement is Activated/Approved the Program is Activated.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Terminated</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>From Activated</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Is manually set on the agreement. The versioned (original) Agreement status. Status Category is set to Superseded.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Cancel</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>From In Amendment </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>When the agreement is In Amendment, it can be canceled. The In Amendment version is deleted and the agreement Being Amended is re-activated along with originally activated programs.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </tbody>
            </tgroup>
         </table>
      </p>
      <p>When you create a program from an agreement, the program will inherit all the above Status from the Agreement alongside, Account, Start Date and End Date. For example, if a user performs Generate action and the Status category is Request, the program inherits the same Status as Request from the Contract.</p>
      <p>As soon as the contract is in Activate action, the system will automatically update the Status of a Program to Activated.</p>
      <p>After the Contract is activated and the Program is in In Effect/Activated status, a user cannot edit the attributes.</p>
      <note type="note">
         <p>Only Amending Changes (like Add Participants) are allowed on the contract.</p>
      </note>
      <p>Programs have their own statuses which are managed through the Agreement Life Cycle and through jobs that are scheduled as needed.</p>
